    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Ezekiel",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 3,
        "summary": "Ezekiel is made a watchman unto the house of Israel\u2014The blood of Israel is required at his hand unless he raises the warning voice.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Moreover he said unto me, Son of man, eat that thou findest; eat this roll, and go speak unto the house of Israel.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0scroll.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "So I opened my mouth, and he caused me to eat that roll.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he said unto me, Son of man, cause thy belly to eat, and fill thy bowels with this roll that I give thee. Then did I eat it; and it was in my mouth as honey for sweetness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 15:16; Ezek. 2:8; Rev. 10:10 (9\u201310).",
                        "start": 121,
                        "end": 124
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 125,
                        "end": 128
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And he said unto me, Son of man, go, get thee unto the house of Israel, and speak with my words unto them.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For thou art not sent to a people of a strange speech and of an hard language, but to the house of Israel;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Not to many people of a strange speech and of an hard language, whose words thou canst not understand. Surely, had I sent thee to them, they would have hearkened unto thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 11:21 (21, 23).",
                        "start": 152,
                        "end": 161
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But the house of Israel will not hearken unto thee; for they will not hearken unto me: for all the house of Israel are impudent and hardhearted.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hardheartedness; Stubbornness.",
                        "start": 132,
                        "end": 143
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 118
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, I have made thy face strong against their faces, and thy forehead strong against their foreheads.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "As an adamant harder than flint have I made thy forehead: fear them not, neither be dismayed at their looks, though they be a rebellious house.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0diamond.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 121,
                        "end": 123
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Moreover he said unto me, Son of man, all my words that I shall speak unto thee receive in thine heart, and hear with thine ears.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And go, get thee to them of the captivity, unto the children of thy people, and speak unto them, and tell them, Thus saith the Lord God; whether they will hear, or whether they will forbear.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then the spirit took me up, and I heard behind me a voice of a great rushing, saying, Blessed be the glory of the Lord from his place.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Spirit of; Guidance, Divine.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 85
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I heard also the noise of the wings of the living creatures that touched one another, and the noise of the wheels over against them, and a noise of a great rushing.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0sound.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 7
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "So the spirit lifted me up, and took me away, and I went in bitterness, in the heat of my spirit; but the hand of the Lord was strong upon me.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then I came to them of the captivity at Tel-abib, that dwelt by the river of Chebar, and I sat where they sat, and remained there astonished among them seven days.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass at the end of seven days, that the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Son of man, I have made thee a watchman unto the house of Israel: therefore hear the word at my mouth, and give them warning from me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Delegation of Responsibility; Watchman.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Priesthood, Magnifying Callings within.",
                        "start": 117,
                        "end": 124
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When I say unto the wicked, Thou shalt surely die; and thou givest him not warning, nor speakest to warn the wicked from his wicked way, to save his life; the same wicked man shall die in his iniquity; but his blood will I require at thine hand.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 33:14.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Watch.",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Justice.",
                        "start": 181,
                        "end": 184
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sin.",
                        "start": 192,
                        "end": 200
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Accountability.",
                        "start": 223,
                        "end": 230
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 171,
                        "end": 174
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Yet if thou warn the wicked, and he turn not from his wickedness, nor from his wicked way, he shall die in his iniquity; but thou hast delivered thy soul.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prophets, Mission of; Warn.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Again, When a righteous man doth turn from his righteousness, and commit iniquity, and I lay a stumblingblock before him, he shall die: because thou hast not given him warning, he shall die in his sin, and his righteousness which he hath done shall not be remembered; but his blood will I require at thine hand.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 18:24.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 33:12 (12\u201313, 18).",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 6:21; Ezek. 14:4 (3\u20137); 2\u00a0Ne. 26:20.",
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 109
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Nevertheless if thou warn the righteous man, that the righteous sin not, and he doth not sin, he shall surely live, because he is warned; also thou hast delivered thy soul.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 1:4.",
                        "start": 130,
                        "end": 136
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And the hand of the Lord was there upon me; and he said unto me, Arise, go forth into the plain, and I will there talk with thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 8:4.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then I arose, and went forth into the plain: and, behold, the glory of the Lord stood there, as the glory which I saw by the river of Chebar: and I fell on my face.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 1:28.",
                        "start": 148,
                        "end": 152
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then the spirit entered into me, and set me upon my feet, and spake with me, and said unto me, Go, shut thyself within thine house.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But thou, O son of man, behold, they shall put bands upon thee, and shall bind thee with them, and thou shalt not go out among them:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will make thy tongue cleave to the roof of thy mouth, that thou shalt be dumb, and shalt not be to them a reprover: for they are a rebellious house.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 24:27.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 131,
                        "end": 134
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But when I speak with thee, I will open thy mouth, and thou shalt say unto them, Thus saith the Lord God; He that heareth, let him hear; and he that forbeareth, let him forbear: for they are a rebellious house.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prophecy; Teaching with the Spirit.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prophets, Mission of.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 187,
                        "end": 190
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}